{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3533611,"name":"","username":"daniel3","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/a4c791/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-19T23:15:00.665Z","cooked":"<p>Hello!<br>
It’s our first season using pathplanner and we are trying to use pathfinding in tele-op mode.<br>
Our idea is to use the pathfinding to go from the actual position of the robot to other pose in the field, like the coral station or the reef. But we are having an issue to stop the command. For example, we would like to while a button is pressed the robot will run the pathfinding command and if we release the button it should stop.</p>
<p>It’s a code example that we tried but It do not stop the pathfinding if we release the button.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new JoystickButton(Joystick1, OIConstants.kCollectCoralButtonIdx).whileTrue(AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(FieldPoses.kCoralBlueLeft, AutoConstants.constraints));
</code></pre>
<p>Like it do not worked as expected, we tried to create other command and run the Pathfinding command methods inside it, we have here too some logic to find which coral station have the shortest distance from the robot.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public class AutoCollectCmd extends Command {
    private final SwerveSubsystem swerveSubsystem;

    private Command command;
    private Pose2d pose;

    public AutoCollectCmd(SwerveSubsystem swerveSubsystem) {
        this.swerveSubsystem = swerveSubsystem;

        addRequirements(swerveSubsystem);
    }

    @Override
    public void initialize() {
        Pose2d currentPose = swerveSubsystem.getPoseEstimator();
        Translation2d currentTranslation = currentPose.getTranslation();

        if (currentTranslation.getDistance(FieldPoses.kCoralBlueLeft.getTranslation()) &lt;
            currentTranslation.getDistance(FieldPoses.kCoralBlueRight.getTranslation())) {
            pose = FieldPoses.kCoralBlueLeft;
            System.out.println("Left!");

        } else {
            pose = FieldPoses.kCoralBlueRight;
            System.out.println("Right!");
        }

        command = AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(pose, AutoConstants.constraints);
        command.initialize();
    }

    @Override
    public void execute() {
        command.execute();

    }

    @Override
    public void end(boolean interrupted) {
        command.end(interrupted);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean isFinished() {
        return command.isFinished();
    }
}

</code></pre>
<p>It worked fine and the Pathfinding now just run while the button is pressed, but now we have other problem. It is not always but sometimes the Pathfinding follow only the last path, for example if a press the button It’s do nothing and if I move the robot and press again It follow the last path that was create before, but with the actual position, so it goes pretty fast to adjust the path using the last one as reference.</p>
<p>If anyone has any suggestions, we’d appreciate it.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-02-19T23:15:00.665Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":146,"reads":175,"readers_count":174,"score":765.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":492381,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfinding-while-button-is-pressed-in-tele-op","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73610,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfinding-while-button-is-pressed-in-tele-op/492381/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3533946,"name":"Martin Nemaric","username":"Martini159","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/278dde/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-20T05:35:10.450Z","cooked":"<p>It’s tough to say without doing some debugging in your console, but I think your issue might stem from the fact that the <code>AutoCollectCmd</code> is itself a command, and it then goes on to actually create a command <em>inside</em> itself. This not usually something we want to do.</p>
<p>Rather than create a command class, you can using command factories in your drive subsystem.</p>
<p>I would try putting the following methods into your swerve subsystem:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command pathfindToPose (Supplier&lt;Pose2d&gt; _poseSupplier) {
  return new DeferredCommand(
    () -&gt; AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(_poseSupplier.get(), AutoConstants.constraints),
    Set.of(this)
  );  
}

public Pose2d getDesiredPose () {
 //Put your logic here for figuring out what pose you want to go to
 //For you, this looks related to determining which coral station you are closest to
 //Just make sure this returns a Pose2d! :)
}

public Command goToCoralStation () {
  return pathfindToPose(() -&gt; getDesiredPose());
}
</code></pre>
<p>Then bind <code>goToCoralStation</code> to a button with something like the following (based on the first bit of code you shared).</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new JoystickButton(Joystick1, OIConstants.kCollectCoralButtonIdx).whileTrue(swerveSubsystem.goToCoralStation());

</code></pre>
<p>You could also do two different button bindings, one for each coral station. Something like…</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new JoystickButton(Joystick1, OIConstants.kCoralLeft).whileTrue(swerveSubsystem.pathfindToPose(() -&gt; FieldPoses.kCoralBlueLeft));
new JoystickButton(Joystick1, OIConstants.kCoralRight).whileTrue(swerveSubsystem.pathfindToPose(() -&gt; FieldPoses.kCoralBlueRight));
</code></pre>
<p>Hopefully this provides a little bit of a framework that will get you to a solution!</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-02-20T05:35:10.450Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":24,"reads":137,"readers_count":136,"score":182.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":492381,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pathfinding-while-button-is-pressed-in-tele-op","display_username":"Martin Nemaric","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":56673,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pathfinding-while-button-is-pressed-in-tele-op/492381/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3534024,"name":"","username":"daniel3","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/a4c791/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-20T13:01:16.336Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you for the help! We’ve already implemented your suggestions, and it worked pretty well. However, we’re still facing an issue with pathfinding trying to follow the previous trajectory. What happens is that when I press the button, the robot tries to follow the last path, but using the current position. This causes it to move too fast in order to “correct” the error relative to the path it’s using as a reference.</p>
